The BIOS is firmware/software installed on your motherboard that includes a setup module which you can usually enable by hitting delete or another key (read your manual) during the initial power-on sequence.
It is where you tell the system about new devices or it tells you it has recognized new devices (or hasn't) when you add/change key hardware like drives, CDROM, etc..
It has many other functions and you should read your computer manual and learn about them.
